   <note type="content">Titles derived from identifications in scrapbooks from which photographs were removed.</note>
   <note type="biographical/historical" displayLabel="Biographical Note">The Great Southern Lumber Company was chartered in Pennsylvania on January 17, 1902. Between 1902 and 1905, the owners purchased vast areas of long-leaf virgin pine timber in Louisiana. In 1906, the Goodyear Family, who were the principal owners, erected a sawmill on the Bogue Lusa Creek in Washington Parish, and began the town of Bogalusa. From these beginnings grew the Great Southern Lumber Company, the largest sawmill in the world from its opening in 1908 until 1938, when it ceased operation. It was also the largest mill sawing yellow pine during its existence. </note>
